      • initialize

        public void initialize(int accountID,
                       int zoneID,
                       java.lang.String position,
                       android.content.Context context,
                       AdListener listener)
        Create a simple banner without custom data. Use if you do not need to set any details such as custom extras, user location, coppa etc.
        Parameters:
        accountID - Your Phunware Account ID.
        zoneID - The Zone you'd like a placement from.
        position - A string representing the screen location at which to show the banner I.E BOTTOM_CENTER. (com.phunware.android.Positions)
        context - The context in which to show the banner.
        listener - Event listener for Ad related events.

      • initialize

        public void initialize(AdRequest request,
                       java.lang.String position,
                       android.content.Context context,
                       AdListener listener)
        Create a banner with custom data (AdRequest object). Use if you want to specify any custom data in the ad request E.G. coppa
        Parameters:
        request - An AdRequest object, containing details required for mediation.
        position - A string representing the screen location at which to show the banner I.E BOTTOM_CENTER. (com.phunware.android.Positions)
        context - The context in which to show the banner.
        listener - Event listener for Ad related events.
